Package Users

Class Applicant

java.lang.Object
Users.User
Users.Applicant
Direct Known Subclasses:
Officer
public class Applicant extends User
Applicant class represents an applicant in the system. It extends the User class and includes attributes such as application and enquiry list.

2025-04-23

    • applyForProject

      public boolean applyForProject(Projects.Project project, String flatType)
      Applicant applies for a project Checks if the applicant has an active application and if they are an officer for the project. If not, creates a new application and adds it to the applicant's application list. Also adds user to the project's access control list with read permission.
      Parameters:
      project -
      flatType -
      Returns:
      True if application is successful, false otherwise

    • viewApplicationStatus

      public void viewApplicationStatus()
      Applicant views their application status If the applicant has an active application, it displays the project name, neighbourhood, flat type applied, and application status. If not, it informs the user that there is no active application to view.

    • withdrawApplication

      public boolean withdrawApplication()
      Withdraws the application for the applicant Checks if the applicant has an active application. If so, sets the withdrawal status to pending. If not, informs the user that there is no active application to withdraw from.
